[SN]TITLE[SN]
Teenage girls racially abused in Belfast

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police are appealing for information after three teenage girls were racially abused in Belfast city centre.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
It happened at Donegall Square West at around 21:00 BST on Saturday evening.
The girls were sitting on benches beside the city hall when a blonde-haired woman, thought to be in her late teens or 20s, approached them.
Video footage of the woman allegedly shouting racial abuse has been shared on social media.
The PSNI arrived at the scene shortly after the incident but were unable to find the woman.
